{
  "answer": "**The Falsafa corpus includes a partial translation of *Manusmṛti* (attributed to Manu), but Chapter 11 is limited to verses 1–6 only.**[^1]\n\nVerse 11.74 is not present in the available text, and no matching content appears in searches across the corpus. Chapter 11 discusses classifications of Brahmins, gifts, and related topics in these early verses,[^2] but the full chapter (traditionally ~266 verses on penances, expiations, etc.) is not covered here.\n\nIf you're seeking traditional references, Manu 11.74 typically addresses a specific penance (e.g., for certain thefts or violations, like *cāndrāyaṇa* or similar), but that's outside this corpus.\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti*, metadata overview ([/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/translation/#metadata](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/translation/#metadata)).\n[^2]: *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 11 ([/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/11/translation/](works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/11/translation/)).",
